        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-16 14:34:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> Brinda - please review.  This seems 'technically' correct, but I\n > wanted to verify there's no use case where we'd want to create an\n > instance of RecipeParser (if we did, this change would cause it to\n > throw an exception).\n\nUtility classes, which are a collection of static members, are not meant to be instantiated. They should therefore not have public constructors. (squid : S1118)\n\nI prefer empty private constructor, If there is now other Sonar Violations.",
        "patchset_number": 1
